### 1. LU Decomposition

If you have a large system of linear equations and you need to solve it multiple times with different right-hand side vectors, you can use LU decomposition to factorize the matrix once and then solve the system multiple times using forward and backward substitution.

```python
import numpy as np

def lu_decomposition(matrix):
    n = matrix.shape[0]
    lu = np.zeros((n, n))
    for i in range(n):
        for j in range(i, n):
            s = sum(lu[i, k] * matrix[k, j] for k in range(i))
            lu[i, j] = matrix[i, j] - s
        for j in range(i, n):
            if i != j:
                s = sum(lu[k, j] * matrix[i, k] for k in range(i))
                lu[i, j] = (matrix[i, j] - s) / lu

